bug.short_desc: [abrt] firewall-config: wl_log(): python2.7 killed by SIGTRAP

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: I pressed the menu button "reload firewalld" in the "options" menu of firewall GUI.
Version-Release number of selected component: firewall-config-0.3.13-5.fc22
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.5.1 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/bin/python -Es /usr/bin/firewall-config crash_function: wl_log executable: /usr/bin/python2.7 global_pid: 9740 kernel: 4.0.1-300.fc22.x86_64 runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000 var_log_messages: [System Logs]:\n-- Logs begin at Sa 2014-10-11 21:56:59 CEST, end at Mo 2015-05-04 22:55:13 CEST. --
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #1 wl_log at /lib64/libwayland-client.so.0 #2 wl_closure_marshal at /lib64/libwayland-client.so.0 #3 wl_proxy_marshal_array_constructor at /lib64/libwayland-client.so.0 #4 wl_proxy_marshal_constructor at /lib64/libwayland-client.so.0 #5 gdk_wayland_window_create_subsurface.part at /lib64/libgdk-3.so.0 #6 gdk_wayland_window_show at /lib64/libgdk-3.so.0 #7 gdk_window_show_internal at /lib64/libgdk-3.so.0 #8 gtk_window_map at /lib64/libgtk-3.so.0 #13 gtk_widget_map at /lib64/libgtk-3.so.0 #14 gtk_window_show at /lib64/libgtk-3.so.0
Not present any more on Fedora 24. Since this is a wayland-specific issue and wayland is experimental in F22-F24, the fix doesn't need to be backported.
